## When to use this component

Use the notification banner to draw attention to something that the user needs to do, or something that will affect their use of the service.

For example you could use a notification banner to tell people about:

* a disruption to the service they are using
* an important task that they need to perform soon
* an important change to the document they are reading
* whether an action they performed was successful or not

{{ example({group: "components", item: "notification-banner", example: "variety", html: true, open: true, size: "s"}) }}

## When not to use this component

Only add a notification banner to a page if its message is relevant to that page. Use notifcation banners as little as possible to avoid reducing their impact. 

Don't use notification banners within the body of a document. If you need to draw attention to content within a document, use the [warning text](../warning-text/) or [inset text](../inset-text/) components instead.

Don’t use notification banners to confirm that a user has completed a transaction, use the [confirmation page](/patterns/confirmation-pages/) pattern instead.

## How it works

There are 2 ways to use the notification banner component. You can use HTML or, if you are using Nunjucks or the GOV.UK Prototype Kit, you can use the Nunjucks macro.

